  <Docs since="3">
    <summary>The InputMethodSession interface provides the per-client functionality
 of <c><see cref="T:Android.Views.InputMethods.InputMethod" /></c> that is safe to expose to applications.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">The InputMethodSession interface provides the per-client functionality
 of <c><see cref="T:Android.Views.InputMethods.InputMethod" /></c> that is safe to expose to applications.
 
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">Applications will not normally use this interface themselves, instead
 relying on the standard interaction provided by
 <c><see cref="T:Android.Widget.TextView" /></c> and <c><see cref="T:Android.Widget.EditText" /></c>.
</para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
